# Make Etiology design matrix for dates with R format.

`s_date_Eti` creates design matrices for etiology regressions;

## Usage

``` r
s_date_Eti(Rdate, Y, basis = "ps", dof = ifelse(basis == "ncs", 5, 10), ...)
```

## Arguments

- Rdate:

  a vector of dates of `R` format

- Y:

  Binary case/control status; `1` for case; `0` for controls

- basis:

  `ncs` for natural cubic splines; `ps` for penalized-splines based on
  B-spline basis functions (NB: baker does not recommend setting ncs
  using this function; use splines::ns)

- dof:

  Degree-of-freedom for the bases. For `ncs` basis, `dof` is the number
  of columns; For `ps` basis, the number of columns is `dof` if
  `intercept=TRUE`; `dof-1` if `FALSE`.

- ...:

  Other arguments as in
  [`splines::bs()`](https://rdrr.io/r/splines/bs.html)

## Value

- `Z_Eti` design matrix for etiology regression on dates.
